Target: OntoClassSchedule is designed to represent and manage class schedules in an educational setting. It captures the relationships between sessions, courses, and various types of course offerings.

Comment: A specific class meeting or event, capturing details like timing and association with a particular course.
A structured unit of study or training, encompassing various sessions and topics.
A hands-on, practical session focused on experiments or activities, typically associated with scientific or technical subjects.
An interactive session designed for detailed discussion, problem-solving, or study on specific topics.
A presentation or discussion-based session where specific topics are explored in-depth, often with guest speakers or experts.
A formal instructional session where content is delivered to students, primarily through speech and visual aids.
Indicates the specific day of the week on which a session occurs, such as Monday or Tuesday.
Specifies the time when a session begins, without referencing a specific date.
Denotes the time when a session concludes, without referencing a specific date.
Establishes a relationship between a session and the course to which it belongs.
Provides additional notes, comments, or observations related to a specific course.
Indicates the official name or title of a course.
Represents the unique identifier or code assigned to a course for organizational purposes.
